olive oil
1 carrot
1 potato
2 clove garlic
1 sprig spring onion
1 bunch(es) Asian Greens
1 tin sweetcorn
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 packet chicken thigh
3 cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet cornflour

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Thinly slice spring onion. Roughly chop Asian greens. Drain the sweetcorn.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Heat a large saucepan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook garlic & herb seasoning and garlic, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add chicken thigh, the water, chicken-style stock powder, the soy sauce, sesame oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook until chicken is cooked through, 5-10 minutes.
• Using tongs, remove chicken from saucepan and set aside on a chopping board.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Shred chicken using two forks.
• In a small bowl, combine cornflour and a splash of water, then stir until dissolved.

TIP: Slice the chicken if you prefer

• When the veggies are done, return chicken to the saucepan along with the charred corn, roasted veggies, Asian greens and cornflour mixture. Simmer over medium-high heat, stirring, until the sauce has thickened slightly, 2-3 minutes.

• Divide shredded chicken and sweetcorn soup between bowls.
• Sprinkle over spring onion to serve. Enjoy!